House Resolution 168
By: Representatives Holly of the 116th, Berry of the 56th, and Bell of the 75th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Dr. David A. Thomas upon his retirement from Morehouse
2 College; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Dr. David A. Thomas has long been recognized for the vital role that he has
4 played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to the welfare of the students,
5 faculty, and staff of Morehouse College; and
6 WHEREAS, installed in 2018, Dr. Thomas led a dynamic, purpose-driven, and
7 record-breaking tenure as the 12th president of Morehouse College; and
8 WHEREAS, guided by his expertise, the college transitioned from experiencing structural
9 deficits to funding significant campus projects, enhancing its technology infrastructure, and
10 offering competitive pay to its employees; and
11 WHEREAS, he oversaw an unprecedented fund-raising acceleration that has generated over
12 $240 million, a giving total higher than any other president in the college's 157 year-long
13 history; and
